\p
\v 13 Jesus went out again to the sea; and all the people came to him, and he taught them. 
\v 14 As he went along, he saw Levi, the son of Alphaeus, sitting in the tax office, and said to him, \wj ‘Follow \+w me\+w*.’\wj* Levi got up and followed him. 
\p
