\v 16 When the teachers of the Law belonging to the party of the Pharisees saw that he was eating in the company of such people, they said to his disciples, ‘Why does he eat with the tax collectors and outcasts?’ 
\v 17 Hearing this, Jesus said, \wj ‘\+w It\+w* \+w is\+w* \+w not\+w* \+w those\+w* \+w who\+w* \+w are\+w* \+w healthy\+w* \+w who\+w* \+w need\+w* \+w a\+w* doctor, \+w but\+w* \+w those\+w* \+w who\+w* \+w are\+w* \+w ill\+w*. \+w I\+w* \+w did\+w* \+w not\+w* \+w come\+w* \+w to\+w* \+w call\+w* \+w the\+w* religious, \+w but\+w* \+w the\+w* outcast.’\wj* 
\p
